we would put our faith and trust in Jesus Christ.

00:18:53.285 --> 00:18:58.070
The trust that he is your son, he died for our sin, and he rose from the dead.

00:18:58.250 --> 00:19:06.999
And perhaps this could be the first day that we partake of communion with the remembrance of all that Jesus has done for us.

00:19:07.719 --> 00:19:18.930
And so Father, I pray that you would make this a very significant time for each and every one of us, no matter how long we've been Christians, and that we would renew a sense of your love and your grace for us.

00:19:19.330 --> 00:19:25.027
and that that would propel us and compel us to live lives that are honoring and pleasing to you.

00:19:25.589 --> 00:19:27.094
We ask it all in Jesus' name.

00:19:28.037 --> 00:19:28.498
Amen.
